UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426681800106
AB  - This study offers a theory and technique for the derivation of a new concept for bank output in an effort to bridge a gap in banking theory. Banks as costs minimizing firms is the background for most bank cost studies, however, this element plays very little explicit role in analyzing banks within the monetary process. This gap might be bridged by extracting the flow of moneyness embodied in bank activities and using it as the output measure. This measure might then be used to develop a comprehensive theory of banks as producers as well as vehicles for the implementation of monetary policy.
