UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426681800015
AB  - The rationality of requiring compensating balances in commercial lending is a long-standing controversy. This paper demonstrates that compensating balance requirements can be either rational or irrational and derives the conditions under which each may occur. The model presented is capable of explaining, illustrating, and resolving (analytically and graphically) the apparent inconsistency among conclusions of previous studies. In addition, the model entertains questions of optimality in borrowing arrangements.
