AB  - Within the term structure of interest rate literature, three different quantifications of the expectations hypothesis are commonly employed. This paper demonstrates under very general conditions that the three quantifications are inconsistent. Each quantification implies a different price for the same bond. The paper concludes with a brief discussion of both the theoretical and empirical implications of these results.
