UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S037842668180009X
AB  - In reply to Fama's (1975) tests on market efficiency and the constancy of the ex ante real rate, Nelson and Schwert (1977) have demonstrated that the tests were not sufficiently powerful. We have shown that all the structural parameters of their model are identifiable; as such, the random forecasting errors do not confound the problem of identifying variations in the real rate. We estimated the Mundell effect and demonstrated that in terms of in-sample predictive efficiency, the simple Fisherian framework to generate real rates fairs quite well once rationality is imposed.
